The paper deals with the task of 3D human pose estimation from 2D joint locations, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method based on generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a popular technique in machine learning (ML) and falls under the sub-category cs.LG. The paper also involves unsupervised learning, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (AI) and can be categorized under cs.AI. The paper also deals with projecting 3D poses onto a 2D plane, which is a topic in computer graphics (GR) and can be categorized under cs.GR. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on two datasets, which involves data processing and analysis, and can be categorized under cs.MM (multimedia).
